title: Way Of The Lawless
creator: Max Brand
description: LibriVox recording of Way Of The Lawless, by Max Brand. Read by Richard Kilmer. Young Andrew Lanning made one mistake in the beginning, and now the most feared lawman in the mountain desert, Hal Dozier, is on his trail and will stop at nothing to bring the outlaw Lanning to justice. But is Andrew guilty of all the things he is being accused of? There is one, a pretty young girl, who doesn't believe all she hears about him. Again, Max Brand shows us why he is the master of the pulp western. (Introduction by Richard Kilmer) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; adventure; fiction; westerns; United States
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: Richard Kilmer is one of the best readers on Librivox, much better than most pros.  Fascinating book...the myth of the old west...only one thing...I wish someone would explain the twist ending to me because I don't get it.
